                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/577: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-04-11T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1927—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 8, 6 p.m. This Government is prepared to pay its proportionate share
                    for the purpose of chartering ship to take care of you and your staff while you
                    remain at Hankow. Department desires to know what this share would be. You must
                    understand that this Government has no funds for the purpose of chartering a
                    ship as a place of refuge for Americans at Hankow for an indefinite time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
